column5: A related resource.
An established standard to which the described resource conforms.
A related resource that is substantially the same as the pre-existing described resource, but in another format.
A related resource that is included either physically or logically in the described resource.
A related resource that is a version, edition, or adaptation of the described resource.
A related resource that is substantially the same as the described resource, but in another format.
A related resource in which the described resource is physically or logically included.
A related resource that references, cites, or otherwise points to the described resource.
A related resource that supplants, displaces, or supersedes the described resource.
A related resource that requires the described resource to support its function, delivery, or coherence.
A related resource of which the described resource is a version, edition, or adaptation.
A related resource that is referenced, cited, or otherwise pointed to by the described resource.
A related resource that is supplanted, displaced, or superseded by the described resource.
A related resource that is required by the described resource to support its function, delivery, or coherence.
A related resource from which the described resource is derived.
A summary of the resource.
Information about who can access the resource or an indication of its security status.
The method by which items are added to a collection.
The frequency with which items are added to a collection.
The policy governing the addition of items to a collection.
A class of entity for whom the resource is intended or useful.
An entity responsible for making contributions to the resource.
The spatial or temporal topic of the resource, the spatial applicability of the resource, or the jurisdiction under which the resource is relevant.
An entity primarily responsible for making the resource.
An account of the resource.
A class of entity, defined in terms of progression through an educational or training context, for which the described resource is intended.
The size or duration of the resource.
The file format, physical medium, or dimensions of the resource.
A process, used to engender knowledge, attitudes and skills, that the described resource is designed to support.
A language of the resource.
A legal document giving official permission to do something with the resource.
An entity that mediates access to the resource and for whom the resource is intended or useful.
The material or physical carrier of the resource.
A statement of any changes in ownership and custody of the resource since its creation that are significant for its authenticity, integrity, and interpretation.
An entity responsible for making the resource available.
Information about rights held in and over the resource.
A person or organization owning or managing rights over the resource.
Spatial characteristics of the resource.
The topic of the resource.
A list of subunits of the resource.
Temporal characteristics of the resource.
The nature or genre of the resource.
Critical or explanatory note for a Document.
Relates a document to another document that cites the first document.
Relates a document to another document that is cited by the first document as reference, comment, review, quotation or for another purpose.
Relates a review document to a reviewed thing (resource, item, etc.).
The resource in which another resource is reproduced.
A legal decision that affirms a ruling.
A legal decision that reverses a ruling.
A legal decision on appeal that takes action on a case (affirming it, reversing it, etc.).
Relates a document to some transcribed original.
Relates a translated document to the original document.
A location that something is based near, for some broadly human notion of near.
A depiction of some thing.
A thing depicted in this representation.
An organization funding a project or person.
An image that can be used to represent some thing (ie. those depictions which are particularly representative of something, eg. one's photo on a homepage).
A document that this thing is the primary topic of.
A person known by this person (indicating some level of reciprocated interaction between the parties).
A logo representing some thing.
Something that was made by this agent.
An agent that made this thing.
Indicates a member of a Group.
A page or document about this thing.
The primary topic of some page or document.
A derived thumbnail image.
A property representing an abridgment of an expression.
A property representing an expression that is abridged.
A property representing an adaption of a work or expression.
A property representing a work or expression that is adapted.
A property representing an alternative to a manifestation.
A property representing a manifestation that is alternated.
A property representing an arrangement of an expression.
A property representing an expression that is arranged.
A property representing a complement to a work or expression.
A property representing a work or expression that is complemented.
A property representing an entity in some way responsible for the creation of a work.
A property representing a work that was in some way created by of an entity.
A property representing a manifestation that embodies an expression.
A property representing an expression that is embodied by a manifestation.
A property representing an item that is an exemplar of a manifestation.
A property representing the manifestation that is exemplified by a item.
A property representing an imitation of a work or expression.
A property representing a work or expression that is imitated.
A property representing an entity that owns an item.
A property representing an item that is in some way owned an entity.
A property representing a part of an endeavour.
A property representing an endeavour incorporating an endeavour.
A property representing an entity in some way responsible for producing a manifestation.
A property representing a manifestation that was in some way produced an entity.
A property representing an expression that is an intellectual or artistic realization of a work.
A property representing the work that has been realized by an expression.
A property representing an entity in some way responsible for realizing an expression.
A property representing an expression that was in some way realized by an entity.
A property representing a recongifuration of an item.
A property representing an item that is reconfigured.
A property representing another endeavour that is related in some way to an endeavour.
A property representing a reproduction of a manifestation or item.
A property representing a manifestation or item that is reproduced.
A property representing an entity in some way responsible for an endeavour.
A property representing an endeavour that is the responsibility of an entity.
A property representing a revision of an expression.
A property representing an expression that is revised.
A property representing a successor to a work or expression.
A property representing a work or expression that is succeeded.
A property representing a summarization of a work or expression.
A property representing a work or expression that is summarized.
A property representing a supplement to a work or expression.
A property representing a work or expression that is supplemented.
A property representing a transformation of a work or expression.
A property representing a work or expression that is transformed.
A property representing a translation of an expression.
A property representing an expression that is translated.
A person that takes the parent role in an event
A person, group or organization that participates in a relationship for some time
A relationship that a person, group or organization participates in for some time
An agent that is involved in an event as an employer
A person that officiates at a ceremonial event.
An organization that plays a role in an event.

A person that takes the primary and most important role in an event. For example the principal in a Birth event would be the child being born and the principal in a Burial event would be the deceased person.
A person that is involved in a event as a partner in a relationship.
A person that witnesses and can bear testimony to the occurrence of an event.
A person that is present at and observes the occurrence of at least part of an event.
An event that occurs while this event is occurring. The events need not start or conclude at the same times.
An event that starts at some time after this event.
An event that occurs and concludes at some time before this event.
An event that starts immediately after this event.
An event that occurs and concludes immediately before this event.
